Several substations in Pietermaritzburg tripped on Monday morning causing a massive electricity outage in the City. Substations at Riverside, Woodburn, Copesville, Haniville and Bishopstowe are among those that tripped- affecting surrounding areas. According to Msunduzi Municipality, electricity teams are currently busy replacing all affected transformers. Residents were again left wondering why there was an electricity outage again while some said attempts to contact the municipality were fruitless. Some of the affected areas had no electricity over the weekend.